.SH NAME
\*LXmSetFontUnits \*O\(em A function that sets the font unit value for a display
.iX "XmSetFontUnits"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Xm/Xm.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void XmSetFontUnits (\*Vdisplay, h_value, v_value\*L)
.ta .5i 1.5i
	Display	\*V* display\*L;
	int	\*Vh_value\*L;
	int	\*Vv_value\*L;
.wH .fi
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LXmSetFontUnits\*O provides an external function to initialize font unit
values.  Applications may want to specify resolution-independent data based
on a global font size.  This function must be called before any widgets with
resolution-independent data are created.  See the \*LXmNunitType\*O
resource description in the manual pages for
\*LXmGadget\*O, \*LXmManager\*O, and \*LXmPrimitive\*O for more information
on resolution independence.
.PP
This function sets the font units for all screens on the display.
\*LXmSetFontUnits\*O is obsolete and exists for compatibility with
previous releases.
Instead of using this function, provide initial values or call
\*LXtSetValues\*O for the XmScreen resources \*LXmNhorizontalFontUnit\*O
and \*LXmNverticalFontUnit\*O.
.nL
.ne 12
.VL 1.25i 
.LI "\*Vdisplay\*O"
Defines the display for which this font unit value is to be applied.
.LI "\*Vh_value\*O"
Specifies the value to be used for horizontal
units in the conversion calculations.
.LI "\*Vh_value\*O"
Specifies the value to be used for vertical
units in the conversion calculations.
.LE 
